This gives the integral: 

\begin{eqnarray*}
\int \frac{x^2 - 20}{x^2 + 16} \, dx &=& \int \frac{(u - 16) - 20}{u} \cdot \frac{du}{2x} \\
&=& \int \frac{u - 36}{u} \cdot \frac{du}{2x} \\
&=& \int \frac{1}{2} \left(1 - \frac{36}{u}\right) \, du.
\end{eqnarray*}

Evaluating this integral leads to: 

\begin{eqnarray*}
\frac{1}{2} \left( u - 36 \ln |u| \right) + C \\
= \frac{1}{2} \left( x^2 + 16 - 36 \ln |x^2 + 16| \right) + C.
\end{eqnarray*} 

